==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Externality
<hw>Ex`ter*nal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>State of being
external; exteriority</def>; <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>separation from
the perceiving mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pressure or resistance necessarily supposes <qex>externality</qex>
in the thing which presses or resists.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>externalization</ent>⟦br⟧
